<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-05-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-05-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="74" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d74">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">893.24/1721</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Under Secretary of State</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Stettinius</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi><note n="72" xml:id="d74fn72">Marginal notation by the Secretary of
                            State: “Why not consider lending first—in view of trouble about Italian
                            transfers. C[ordell] H[ull].”</note>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-05-24">May 24, 1944</date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>On your return to the office you will wish to give consideration to the
                        Department’s position on the question of the transfer of eight naval vessels
                        to China.</p>
                    <p>I have asked Mr. Grew to analyze the matter thoroughly with the Navy and he
                        will be fully informed and prepared to discuss the matter with you at your
                        convenience.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>E[<hi rend="smallcaps">dward</hi>] S[<hi rend="smallcaps">tettinius</hi>]</signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>